  "detailed_description": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/6b901091561a1063bed4cd82d0c98aa6.poster.avif?t=1768039636\" width=620 height=264 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/6b901091561a1063bed4cd82d0c98aa6.webm?t=1768039636\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/6b901091561a1063bed4cd82d0c98aa6.mp4?t=1768039636\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>You wake up sitting across from a beautiful stranger.<br><br><i>\"There is nothing I want more than to talk to you right now.\"</i><br><br>And so you talk.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/b3d5ecf6172a5edd2f8983ba4bb7228b.webp?t=1768039636\" width=385 height=2 /></span><br><br>Locke(d) is a short, mysterious and atmospheric visual novel with brief point-and-click segments.<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Linear visual novel<br></li><li> ~3000 words<br></li><li> 10-30 minutes of reading</li></ul><br>The game was originally made within 2 weeks, and was heavily inspired by a passage in John Locke's <i>\"An Essay Concerning Human Understanding\"</i>.",
  "about_the_game": "<span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><video class=\"bb_img\" autoplay muted loop playsinline poster=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/6b901091561a1063bed4cd82d0c98aa6.poster.avif?t=1768039636\" width=620 height=264 ><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/6b901091561a1063bed4cd82d0c98aa6.webm?t=1768039636\" type=\"video/webm; codecs=vp9\"><source src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/6b901091561a1063bed4cd82d0c98aa6.mp4?t=1768039636\" type=\"video/mp4\"></video></span><br><br>You wake up sitting across from a beautiful stranger.<br><br><i>\"There is nothing I want more than to talk to you right now.\"</i><br><br>And so you talk.<br><br><span class=\"bb_img_ctn\"><img class=\"bb_img\" src=\"https://shared.akamai.steamstatic.com/store_item_assets/steam/apps/2267810/extras/b3d5ecf6172a5edd2f8983ba4bb7228b.webp?t=1768039636\" width=385 height=2 /></span><br><br>Locke(d) is a short, mysterious and atmospheric visual novel with brief point-and-click segments.<br><br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> Linear visual novel<br></li><li> ~3000 words<br></li><li> 10-30 minutes of reading</li></ul><br>The game was originally made within 2 weeks, and was heavily inspired by a passage in John Locke's <i>\"An Essay Concerning Human Understanding\"</i>.",
